July 19. 1642. An exact relation of two victorious battels fought by the English: wherein they put to flight 2200, and kill'd 700 of the rebels at Cardoughen in the province of Munster; and 500 more at Youghall; at both which places they took a great quantity of ammunition, goods and victuals from the rebels. As it was sent to Mr. Buller, a member of the House of Commons, and another gentleman of quality. Wherein is likewise a true relation of the death of the Lord President. Buller, John, 17th cent. Moore, Thomas, 17th cent.
6 p.
Printed by L.N. and I.F. for E. Husbands and I. Franck, London : [1642]
Consists of 2 letters, written by John Buller and Thomas Moore respectively. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
